                            <comment id="15884775" author="daniel_sun" created="Sun, 26 Feb 2017 14:51:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;parentheses are required when declaring methods.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct code should be as follows:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;ATest &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;extends&lt;/span&gt; TestCase {
  void &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;test methods with dots within its name.dot&apos;&lt;/span&gt;() {}
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15885872" author="paulk" created="Mon, 27 Feb 2017 14:44:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=daniel_sun&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;daniel_sun&quot;&gt;daniel_sun&lt;/a&gt; I believe it&apos;s just a typo in the above snippet. If you look at the link, all the examples have parentheses. And 2.5.0-SNAPSHOT still gives ClassFormatError for your example with the parentheses. To allow the dot we&apos;d need to encode it somehow. I suspect the easiest thing for now would just be to disallow dots for the time being and give a friendly error message.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15885878" author="paulk" created="Mon, 27 Feb 2017 14:47:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I fixed what I believe was the typo in the original description.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15885983" author="daniel_sun" created="Mon, 27 Feb 2017 15:40:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt;  I suspect the easiest thing for now would just be to disallow dots for the time being and give a friendly error message.&lt;br/&gt;
